HTML = Hyper text markUp Language
language = set of rules 
Markup = annotation or tags to show markup content 
HyperText = text used to link multiple pages or one single page linked to another page

uses:
Html =(Description of web pages) Basic building block(skeleton of web) , basically for content creation
CSS = For formatting or appearance 
Javascript = Functionality 

Tags = Keyword to tell browser how to render different elements

Text element , 100 + html Tags available 
Block Element                  and                   Inline element, uses to differentiate specific part of text
Paragraph <p></p>                                       Emphasis <em></em>
heading <h1></h1>                                        Strong Emphasis<strong></strong>
list <ul></ul>                                           Anchor for link  <a></a>
      <article></article>
      <section></section>


Empty tag = self closing tag i.e <br/> , <img/> , <input/>

Lists :- Ordered , Unordered and description Lists.

Attributes = property
 put always in start of a tag
 All elements have Attributes
 uses, provide additional info about elements

 <!DOCTYPE html> tell browser it is htm version5 Document
  lang = "en" tell content of web page in english.
 In head tag we have metadata,  data about data title, characterSet, viewPort(screen of device), style, script, other metadata
    meta tag store info about web page 
 In body tag Actual Content 

<hr> "hr " tag to create line horizontal
<Table>create table <tr>to create row</tr>, <td>tsble colum</td></Table>
first row is thead
above last row for tbody
last row is tfooter/summary
<form>radio , checkbox, description</form>